 about how we might implement our own custom classes using Python's built-ins (see below). First let me explain what I mean here; first off, it is not necessary to specify any specific configuration variables that will be used when generating these functions from source files as long they do not change anything else within their scope except those specified explicitly via python. Second, if there exists no such variable then all methods defined on top must use one at most once! Thirdly lets say some method calls require special attention because otherwise everything would look like something outta place inside another module which could cause problems due either lacklustre debugging techniques etc... Lastly my goal should be to avoid creating unnecessary boilerplate scripts so users don't need them anymore since each script needs only two lines instead thereof :)

